<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"closing">Closing thoughts</h2>



<p>While statistical significance testing is a powerful tool in the arms of=
 a good CRO or UX expert, it is not a panacea or substitute for expertise, =
for well-researched and well-designed tests. It is a fairly complex concept=
 to grasp, apply appropriately, and communicate to uninformed clients. I ho=
pe this post, which is a natural continuation of years of work on A/B testi=
ng statistical theory and methodology, helped shed light on it and can serv=
e as a handy introduction to the matter.</p>



